ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: In the past 2 months, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Had fuzzy memories of events that occurred while you were drinking?
Notes: 0=Never; 1=1 Time; 2=2-3 Times; 3=Weekly; 4=Twice a Week or More; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past 2 months, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Had memories that became clear only when someone/something gave you cues or reminded you later?
Notes: 0=Never; 1=1 Time; 2=2-3 Times; 3=Weekly; 4=Twice a Week or More; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past 2 months, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Been unable to remember what happened the night before because you had been drinking?
Notes: 0=Never; 1=1 Time; 2=2-3 Times; 3=Weekly; 4=Twice a Week or More; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past 2 months, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Not been able to remember large stretches of time while drinking heavily?
Notes: 0=Never; 1=1 Time; 2=2-3 Times; 3=Weekly; 4=Twice a Week or More; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past 2 months, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Suddenly found yourself in a place you don't remember getting to?
Notes: 0=Never; 1=1 Time; 2=2-3 Times; 3=Weekly; 4=Twice a Week or More; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past year, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Had fuzzy memories of events that occurred while you were drinking?
Notes: 0=Never in the past year; 1=At least once in the past year, but less than monthly; 2=Monthly; 3=Weekly; 4=Daily or almost daily; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past year, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Had memories that became clear only when someone/something gave you cues or reminded you later?
Notes: 0=Never in the past year; 1=At least once in the past year, but less than monthly; 2=Monthly; 3=Weekly; 4=Daily or almost daily; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past year, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Been unable to remember what happened the night before because you had been drinking?
Notes: 0=Never in the past year; 1=At least once in the past year, but less than monthly; 2=Monthly; 3=Weekly; 4=Daily or almost daily; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past year, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Not been able to remember large stretches of time while drinking heavily?
Notes: 0=Never in the past year; 1=At least once in the past year, but less than monthly; 2=Monthly; 3=Weekly; 4=Daily or almost daily; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)

ElementDescription: In the past year, as a result of alcohol use, how often have you: Suddenly found yourself in a place you don't remember getting to?
Notes: 0=Never in the past year; 1=At least once in the past year, but less than monthly; 2=Monthly; 3=Weekly; 4=Daily or almost daily; -5 = Item seen but not answered; -999 = Data not submitted (Incomplete, item not seen)
